      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ack to first suggestion. Will address.\n\n\u003e nothing structurally stops it being committed\n\nIn the \"interaction with registries\" section, we make it clear (hopefully!)\nthat the `local-module.cue` file is omitted, which avoids it being published at least.\nWe\u0027d also make the Central Registry reject published modules with such a file present - we perhaps don\u0027t need to make that totally clear here, as it\u0027s more of an implementation concern.\n\nCommit and publish are two quite separate matters, I think. I don\u0027t think it\u0027s possible to stop the file being committed - that\u0027s a matter between the user and their VCS AFAICS. I\u0027m not even sure it\u0027s desirable. For example, I see Go modules that have directory replace statements that reference local directories and that aren\u0027t targeted at being a dependency. That seems like a reasonable use case to me.",
