      "writtenOn": "2026-05-29T14:56:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems to suggest that a wholesale copy of the `module.cue` is required, rather than being a sparse overlay. The wording above (\"When `local-module.cue` is present, the CUE tooling merges information from both files\") seems to suggest the opposite. \n\nWe definitely need to make clear what the intended workflow is.\n\nAnd if it is a sparse overlay approach, then why are we advocating this `cp` command here? It\u0027s not necessary, and requires a whole load of explanatory text caveating what `cue mod tidy` would do to reduce it.",
      "revId": "3246977dd4008d03b285a57cd301568ca766dcb3",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
