        "id": 1007275
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-06-01T16:26:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree that might not be an ideal workflow, although I think it might be a useful one: if I\u0027ve got an existing `module.cue` file, I can easily modify it to add a `replace` directive without starting from scratch and creating a `deps` entry for the module I might want to replace.\n\nThe point I was really trying to get across is that the two files are essentially compatible with one another, but also that from a tooling p.o.v. it\u0027s not just a unification operation (otherwise updating the dependencies manually in one might result in a conflict rather than updating via MVS max-version semantics).\n\nI\u0027ll work on some better wording.",
      "parentUuid": "271f84cc_54ba042b",
      "revId": "3246977dd4008d03b285a57cd301568ca766dcb3",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
